-- ING Groep Selling Canadian Commercial Real Estate Portfolio, Globe Says
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-07-06T11:35:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/ing-groep-selling-canadian-commercial-real-estate-portfolio-globe-says.html

          
          
             ING Groep NV,  the biggest Dutch
financial-services company, is selling a portfolio of warehouses
and industrial properties in Canada to bolster its balance
sheet, the Globe and Mail reported.  
 ING purchased the properties of Summit Real Estate
Investment Trust for C$2.1 billion ($1.98 billion) four years
ago, the newspaper said. The sale, arranged through TD
Securities, could reach up to C$2 billion, the Globe said.  
 ING was hoping to close the sale by June, although itâ€™s
taking longer as possible buyers are trying to find financing,
the newspaper said, citing unidentified people.  
